); West Bengal: kantikuri (
Tribedi CNH-1435
); Malaysia. priapantie (
Curtis 858
).

It is reported that in Thailand the plant is boiled to serve as a decoction for ulcerated throat (
Collins 1380
). Indian collectors reported that the fruits are edible and used as medicinal (
Raji 291
, 
Sengupta 145
). In Penang (Malaysia) the root is used medicinally (
Curtis 858
). For the many uses in traditional medicine in India see section on Uses (pg. 18-20).
